---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';

const siteUrl = 'https://aicostplanner.com';
const currentDate = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0];
const route = '/gpt-image-api-pricing/';
const breadcrumbs = [{ label: 'GPT Image API Pricing', href: route }];
const internalLinks = [
  { href: '/gpt-image-api-cost/', label: 'GPT Image API Cost' },
  { href: '/image-generation-api-pricing/', label: 'Image Generation API Pricing' },
  { href: '/image-generation-api-cost/', label: 'Image Generation API Cost' },
  { href: '/failed-generation-cost/', label: 'Failed Generation Cost' },
];
---

<PageLayout
  title="GPT Image API Pricing Guide"
  description="Understand GPT image API pricing concepts without claiming exact prices unless verified live. Learn what settings and units affect image generation spend."
  canonical={`${siteUrl}${route}`}
  type="article"
  lastUpdated={currentDate}
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Article",
      "headline": "GPT Image API Pricing: What Pricing Units and Settings Affect Image Spend",
      "description": "Understand GPT image API pricing concepts without claiming exact prices unless verified live.",
      "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "AICostPlanner" },
      "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "AICostPlanner", "url": siteUrl },
      "datePublished": currentDate,
      "dateModified": currentDate,
      "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": `${siteUrl}${route}` }
    })} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": siteUrl },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "GPT Image API Pricing", "item": `${siteUrl}${route}` }
      ]
    })} />
  </Fragment>

  <Header />
  <main>
    <section class="hero-dark"><div class="container"><Breadcrumb items={breadcrumbs} /><h1 class="page-title">GPT Image API Pricing</h1><p class="page-meta"><span class="label-mono">Last updated: {currentDate}</span></p></div></section>
    <section class="section-light content-section"><div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="quick-answer"><h2>Quick Answer</h2><p>GPT image API pricing can depend on generated image count, resolution, quality tier, edit operations and retry behavior. Pricing can change, so check live provider pricing before production use.</p></div>
      <h2>What pricing units matter for GPT image</h2><p>GPT image cost is usually framed around generated image count, resolution settings and quality tiers. Understanding these units helps you compare different image API options without conflating pricing with full workflow cost.</p>
      <h2>How pricing differs from cost</h2><p>This page focuses on pricing units and settings. The companion cost page covers full workflow spend including retries, failed moderation and usage record review. Keeping them distinct helps avoid thin duplication.</p>
      <h2>Common pricing variables</h2><ul><li><span class="mono">image</span> per generated output</li><li><span class="mono">resolution</span> larger output may cost more</li><li><span class="mono">quality</span> HD or detail-enhanced settings</li><li><span class="mono">edit</span> inpainting or variation operations</li></ul>
      <h2>Cost risks</h2><p>Retries, moderation failures and unexpected resolution defaults can shift actual spend from initial pricing estimates.</p>
      <h2>Small test checklist</h2><ul class="checklist"><li><span class="checklist-icon">&#10003;</span><span>Test one generation at each quality tier</span></li><li><span class="checklist-icon">&#10003;</span><span>Compare resolution settings with billed usage</span></li><li><span class="checklist-icon">&#10003;</span><span>Record request IDs for every generation</span></li><li><span class="checklist-icon">&#10003;</span><span>Check whether failed or retried jobs were billed</span></li></ul>
      <h2>Common errors / failed tasks</h2><p>Moderation filtering, invalid parameters and retry loops are common sources of unexpected spend. Use logs to confirm billing accuracy.</p>
      <h2>Related pages</h2><div class="link-cards">{internalLinks.map(link => (<a href={link.href} class="link-card"><h4>{link.label}</h4><p>Read the related image topic</p></a>))}</div>
      <div class="ai-summary-block"><div class="ai-summary-label"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 16v-4M12 8h.01"/></svg> AI Summary</div><p>GPT image API pricing often depends on generated image count, resolution, quality tier, edit operations and retry behavior. This page explains pricing concepts without claiming exact live prices. Examples are educational. Check live provider pricing before production use and test small before scaling.</p></div>
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><div class="faq-list"><div class="faq-item"><h3 class="faq-question">Is GPT image pricing per image?</h3><p class="faq-answer">Usually yes, but resolution, quality tier and edit operations can also affect the final bill.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3 class="faq-question">Should I separate pricing and cost pages?</h3><p class="faq-answer">Yes, when one focuses on billing units and settings while the other covers full workflow spend.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3 class="faq-question">Can pricing change?</h3><p class="faq-answer">Yes. Pricing and model availability can change. Always check live provider pricing before production use.</p></div></div>
      <div class="cta-block"><h3>Start with a small prepaid test</h3><p>Create an API key with $1 trial credit, compare model pricing and test GPT image behavior.</p><div class="cta-buttons"><a href="https://app.rutaapi.com/register?lng=en" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Create API Key <span class="btn-subtext">$1 trial credit</span></a><a href="https://app.rutaapi.com/pricing" class="btn btn-secondary-dark" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Compare Model Pricing</a><a href="https://app.rutaapi.com/register?lng=en" class="btn btn-secondary-dark" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Start with a Small Prepaid Test</a></div></div>
    </div></section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .hero-dark { background: var(--color-bg-dark); padding: var(--space-12) 0 var(--space-10); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-bg-dark-border); }
  .hero-dark :global(.breadcrumb) { margin-bottom: var(--space-6); }
  .page-title { font-size: 2.25rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text-dark); line-height: 1.15; margin: 0 0 var(--space-4) 0; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
  .page-meta { margin: 0; }
  .content-section { padding: var(--space-12) 0 var(--space-16); background: var(--color-bg-light); }
  .quick-answer { background: var(--color-bg-light-elevated); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent-blue); padding: var(--space-6); border-radius: 0 var(--radius-md) var(--radius-md) 0; margin-bottom: var(--space-10); }
  .quick-answer h2 { font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .quick-answer p { margin: 0; color: var(--color-text-light); line-height: 1.7; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-light); margin: var(--space-10) 0 var(--space-4); padding-top: var(--space-6); border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); }
  h2:first-of-type { margin-top: 0; padding-top: 0; border-top: none; }
  p { color: var(--color-text-light-muted); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  ul, ol { color: var(--color-text-light-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); padding-left: var(--space-6); }
  li { margin-bottom: var(--space-2); line-height: 1.7; }
  .mono { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.875em; background: var(--color-bg-light-muted); padding: 0.125em 0.375em; border-radius: var(--radius-sm); }
  .checklist { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
  .checklist li { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: var(--space-3); padding: var(--space-3) 0; }
  .checklist-icon { color: var(--color-accent-green); font-weight: bold; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .link-cards { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: var(--space-4); margin-bottom: var(--space-8); }
  .link-card { display: block; padding: var(--space-5); background: var(--color-bg-light-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); border-radius: var(--radius-md); text-decoration: none; transition: all var(--transition-fast); }
  .link-card:hover { border-color: var(--color-accent-blue); transform: translateY(-2px); }
  .link-card h4 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-light); margin: 0 0 var(--space-2) 0; }
  .link-card p { font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-text-light-muted); margin: 0; }
  .ai-summary-block { background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.04), rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.04)); border: 1px solid rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.15); border-radius: var(--radius-xl); padding: var(--space-6); margin: var(--space-10) 0; }
  .ai-summary-label { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--space-2); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--color-accent-cyan); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  .ai-summary-block p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.8; }
  .faq-list { margin-bottom: var(--space-10); }
  .faq-item { padding: var(--space-6) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); }
  .faq-item:first-child { border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); }
  .faq-question { font-size: 1.0625rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .faq-answer { margin: 0; font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .cta-block { text-align: center; padding: var(--space-10); background: var(--color-bg-light-muted); border-radius: var(--radius-xl); margin-top: var(--space-10); }
  .cta-block h3 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .cta-block p { max-width: 40ch; margin: 0 auto var(--space-6); }
  .cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: var(--space-4); justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-accent-blue), var(--color-accent-cyan)); color: white; padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-6); border-radius: var(--radius-md); font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--space-2); transition: all var(--transition-fast); }
  .btn-primary:hover { transform: translateY(-1px); box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.3); color: white; }
  .btn-subtext { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 400; opacity: 0.9; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-2); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); }
  .btn-secondary-dark { background: transparent; color: var(--color-text-light); padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-6); border-radius: var(--radius-md); font-weight: 500; border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); text-decoration: none; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--space-2); transition: all var(--transition-fast); }
  .btn-secondary-dark:hover { border-color: var(--color-accent-blue); color: var(--color-accent-blue); }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .page-title { font-size: 1.75rem; } .link-cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .cta-buttons { flex-direction: column; } .cta-buttons .btn { width: 100%; justify-content: center; } }
</style>
